.SH NAME
HTMLTableSectionElement.deleteRow \- HTMLTableSectionElement:
deleteRow() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]deleteRow()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]HTMLTableSectionElement\f[R] interface removes a specific row
(\f[CR]<tr>\f[R]) from a given \f[CR]<section>\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
deleteRow(index)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]index\f[R]
\f[CR]index\f[R] is an integer representing the row that should be
deleted.
However, the special index \f[CR]\-1\f[R] can be used to remove the very
last row of the section.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]IndexSizeError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if \f[CR]index\f[R] is greater than or equal to the number of
available rows or is a negative value other than \f[CR]\-1\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
In this example, two buttons allow you to add and remove rows from the
table body section; it also updates a \f[CR]<output>\f[R] element with
the number of rows currently in the table.
